defs.docs:
[grpcio] is a Rust implementation of [gRPC], which is a high performance, open source universal RPC
framework that puts mobile and HTTP/2 first. grpcio is built on [gRPC Core] and [futures-rs].

defs.docs: Set maximum number of concurrent incoming streams to allow on a HTTP/2 connection.

defs.name: max_receive_message_len
defs.docs: Set maximum message length that the channel can receive. `usize::MAX` means unlimited.

defs.name: max_send_message_len
defs.docs: Set maximum message length that the channel can send. `-1` means unlimited.

defs.name: max_reconnect_backoff
defs.docs: Set maximum time between subsequent connection attempts.

defs.name: initial_reconnect_backoff
defs.docs: Set time between the first and second connection attempts.

defs.name: https_initial_seq_number
defs.docs: Set initial sequence number for HTTP/2 transports.

defs.name: stream_initial_window_size
defs.docs:
Set amount to read ahead on individual streams. Defaults to 64KB. Larger
 values help throughput on high-latency connections.

defs.name: primary_user_agent
defs.docs:
Set primary user agent, which goes at the start of the user-agent metadata sent on
 each request.

defs.name: reuse_port
defs.docs: Set whether to allow the use of `SO_REUSEPORT` if available. Defaults to `true`.

defs.name: tcp_read_chunk_size
defs.docs: Set the size of slice to try and read from the wire each time.

defs.name: tcp_min_read_chunk_size
defs.docs: Set the minimum size of slice to try and read from the wire each time.

defs.name: tcp_max_read_chunk_size
defs.docs: Set the maximum size of slice to try and read from the wire each time.

defs.name: http2_write_buffer_size
defs.docs:
How much data are we willing to queue up per stream if
 write_buffer_hint is set. This is an upper bound.

defs.name: http2_max_frame_size
defs.docs:
How big a frame are we willing to receive via HTTP/2.
 Min 16384, max 16777215.
 Larger values give lower CPU usage for large messages, but more head of line
 blocking for small messages.

defs.name: http2_bdp_probe
defs.docs: Set whether to enable BDP probing.

defs.name: http2_min_sent_ping_interval_without_data
defs.docs:
Minimum time between sending successive ping frames without receiving any
 data frame.

defs.name: http2_min_recv_ping_interval_without_data
defs.docs:
Minimum allowed time between receiving successive ping frames without
 sending any data frame.

defs.name: http2_max_pings_without_data
defs.docs:
How many pings can we send before needing to send a data frame or header
 frame? (0 indicates that an infinite number of pings can be sent without
 sending a data frame or header frame)

defs.name: http2_max_ping_strikes
defs.docs:
How many misbehaving pings the server can bear before sending goaway and
 closing the transport? (0 indicates that the server can bear an infinite
 number of misbehaving pings)

defs.name: default_compression_algorithm

defs.name: default_compression_level

defs.name: keepalive_time
defs.docs:
After a duration of this time the client/server pings its peer to see
 if the transport is still alive.

defs.name: keepalive_timeout
defs.docs:
After waiting for a duration of this time, if the keepalive ping sender does
 not receive the ping ack, it will close the transport.

defs.name: keepalive_permit_without_calls
defs.docs: Is it permissible to send keepalive pings without any outstanding streams.

ResourceQuota represents a bound on memory and thread usage by the gRPC.
 NOTE: The management of threads created in grpc-core don't use ResourceQuota.
 TODO: Manage the poller threads created in grpc-rs with this ResourceQuota later.
